---
import BaseLayout from '../../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
import NavBar from '../../components/NavBar.astro';
---
<BaseLayout title="Multi-Department Workflows in OpenClaw" description="Gate execution across specialized agents to ensure quality.">
  <NavBar links={[{ href: '/', label: 'Home' }, { href: '/blog/', label: 'Blog' }]} />

  <main class="container">
    <article class="content-shell">
      <p><a href="/use-cases/">← Back to Use Cases</a></p>
      <h1>Multi-Department Workflows</h1>
      <p class="lead">Gate execution across specialized agents to ensure quality.</p>
      
      <h2>What it is</h2>
      <p>OpenClaw supports running multiple isolated subagents, each with specific personas, prompts, and tools. They can pass tasks down a pipeline (e.g., Discovery → Validation → Build → QA → Scale) using strict SLAs and quality gates.</p>
      
      <h2>Why it matters</h2>
      <p>One massive prompt inevitably leads to hallucination and dropped instructions. Specialized agents functioning as "departments" produce higher-quality, auditable work because they cross-check each other before anything reaches production.</p>
    </article>
  </main>
</BaseLayout>
